      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">52.209-12</ph> Certification Regarding Tax Matters.</title>
      <conbody outputclass="provision" class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p class="- topic/p " id="d3133e8">As prescribed in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="9.104-7.dita#FAR_9_104_7"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">9.104-7</xref>(e)</ph>, insert the following provision:</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="Ctr_SmCaps" id="d3149e15">
            <ph rev="FAC 2025-06 October 1, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2024-001?>Certification Regarding Tax Matters (Oct 2025)<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 52.209-12 by revising the date of the provision, and removing from paragraph (b) introductory text “$5.5 million” and adding “$7 million” in its place.?></ph>
         </p>
         <ol id="d3099e29" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3133e19">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						             This provision implements section 523 of Division B of the Consolidated and Further Continuing Appropriations Act, 2015 (Pub. L. 113-235), and similar provisions, if contained in subsequent appropriations acts.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3133e24">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> If the Offeror is proposing a total contract price that will exceed <ph rev="FAC 2025-06 October 1, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2024-001?>$7 million<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 52.209-12 by revising the date of the provision, and removing from paragraph (b) introductory text “$5.5 million” and adding “$7 million” in its place.?></ph> (including options), the Offeror shall certify that, to the best of its knowledge and belief, it</p>
               <ol id="d3099e48" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3133e30">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
								                 Has <cite outputclass="Checkbox"
                              xtrc="52.209-12_d91e33"
                              class="- topic/cite "
                              xtrf="VFI">□</cite> filed all Federal tax returns required during the three years preceding the certification;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3133e38">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
								                 Has not <cite outputclass="Checkbox"
                              xtrc="52.209-12_d91e41"
                              class="- topic/cite "
                              xtrf="VFI">□</cite> been convicted of a criminal offense under the Internal Revenue Code of 1986; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3133e46">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
								                 Has not <cite outputclass="Checkbox"
                              xtrc="52.209-12_d91e49"
                              class="- topic/cite "
                              xtrf="VFI">□</cite>, more than 90 days prior to certification, been notified of any unpaid Federal tax assessment for which the liability remains unsatisfied, unless the assessment is the subject of an installment agreement or offer in compromise that has been approved by the Internal Revenue Service and is not in default, or the assessment is the subject of a non-frivolous administrative or judicial proceeding.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
         <p outputclass="Endofprovision" class="- topic/p ">(End of provision)</p>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
